
/*
 * The code snippet demonstrates how to add nodes to the [args] node within a [sockets.signal] invocation. It uses [add] to append nodes retrieved by [get-nodes] from the [.arguments] node, effectively merging argument nodes into the [args] node for signaling. 
 * 
 * 1. [add] - Appends nodes to the specified target node.
 * 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves nodes from the specified expression, in this case, from [.arguments].
 */
add:x:./*/sockets.signal/*/args
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*
